docs.lead_paragraph: Our dates front Panama reach to the 18th inst. There is no news of the least consequence. The U. S. sloop-of-war Portsmouth, Capt. DORWIN, has returned to Panama, after an absence of nearly seven months, having visited during that period the ports of San Francisco, Monterey, Santa Barbara and, Sari Diego, in California.

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. W. F. ANDERSON, of Newberry, S. C,, left Charleston, on Wednesday, the 16th, apparently in his usual health, was seized on the road with a violent attack of cholera morbus, under which, in the absence of all remedial agents, he continued to Suffer throughout the journey, sank rapidly and died.

docs.lead_paragraph: General PIERCE has done well in selecting such men as MANN, CLAY and FAY, to important positions under the Government. It was a bold stroke that floored the expectations of a thousand and one aspirants for these places, whose chief recommendations were partizan services and their claims for reward; but it is proving to have been an eminently successful one.

byline.original: Correspondence of the New- York Daily Times

docs.lead_paragraph: The latest dates from Oregon, received via San Francisco, are to the 18th February. The gold mines were yielding fair returns. The Portland Times has intelligence from the mines of Yreka, Jacksonville, and Winchester.
